{"questionId":"9076879","questionHtml":"<p>A ring of area <em>S</em> is in a uniform magnetic field <em>X</em>. Initially the magnetic field is perpendicular to&nbsp;the plane of the ring. The ring is rotated by 180° about the axis in time <em>T</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3de60b8745747727333d9cc062ef9d9b6a0dc378.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the average induced emf in the ring?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;0</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{XS}}{{2T}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{XS}}{{T}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><br><br>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2XS}}{{T}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076879","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.33","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A ring of area S is in a uniform magnetic field X. Initially the magnetic field is perpendicular to the plane of the ring. The ring is rotated by 180° about the axis in time T. Wha","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"33","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.1 – Electromagnetic induction","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}